#compdef sugar
# =============================================================================
# sugar — Metaplex Foundation's "Candy Machine Rust CLI" — the
#         official CLI for creating, deploying, and managing
#         Solana NFT Candy Machines (Metaplex's on-chain NFT
#         minting program).  Covers the full Candy Machine
#         lifecycle: asset upload to decentralized storage
#         (Bundlr / Arweave / NFT.Storage / AWS) → config
#         creation → on-chain deployment → guard configuration
#         → minting → reveal of hidden settings collections.
#         Distinguishing from solana-cli (general Solana
#         tooling), anchor (Solana program framework), and
#         other NFT minting tools by:
#           - 17 ROOT SUBCOMMANDS via clap derive:
#               * airdrop      — airdrop NFTs to a list
#               * bundlr       — Bundlr storage operations
#                                (balance / withdraw)
#               * collection   — Candy Machine collection mgmt
#                                (set / withdraw)
#               * config       — config file management
#                                (create / update / set)
#               * deploy       — deploy cache items on-chain
#               * freeze       — freeze guard ops (initialize /
#                                thaw / unlock-funds)
#               * guard        — guard mgmt (add / remove /
#                                show / update / withdraw)
#               * hash         — hash cache for hidden settings
#               * launch       — full deploy workflow
#               * mint         — mint one or more NFTs
#               * reveal       — reveal hidden settings NFTs
#               * show         — display on-chain config
#               * sign         — sign NFT(s) (authority)
#               * upload       — upload assets to storage
#               * validate     — validate asset directory
#               * verify       — verify uploads
#               * withdraw     — withdraw rent from a closed
#                                candy machine
#           - INTERACTIVE PROMPTS via dialoguer — confirmation
#             prompts for destructive ops (deploy / withdraw),
#             input prompts during `sugar config create` for
#             interactive config-file generation, password
#             prompts for keypair encryption, multi-select
#             prompts for guard configuration
#           - STRUCTURED LOGGING via tracing +
#             tracing-bunyan-formatter — logs written as JSON
#             to sugar.log; --log-level controls verbosity
#             (trace/debug/info/warn/error/off)
#           - BUNDLR/ARWEAVE STORAGE INTEGRATION via
#             bundlr-sdk — assets uploaded to permaweb storage;
#             tokenized fee payment in SOL
#           - PRIORITY FEE PARAMETER — --priority-fee on every
#             transaction-submitting command (deploy / mint /
#             airdrop / launch) for Solana priority transactions
#             during congested periods
#           - METAPLEX CANDY GUARD v2 — supports the full
#             Candy Guard v2 spec: addressGate, allowList,
#             botTax, endDate, edition, freezeSolPayment,
#             freezeTokenPayment, gatekeeper, mintLimit,
#             nftBurn, nftGate, nftPayment, programGate,
#             redeemedAmount, solPayment, startDate,
#             thirdPartySigner, token2022Payment, tokenBurn,
#             tokenGate, tokenPayment
#           - CACHE FILE for resumable deployments — sugar
#             maintains a local cache.json tracking which
#             assets have been uploaded + deployed; supports
#             interrupting + resuming long mints
#           - HIDDEN SETTINGS COLLECTIONS — pre-reveal NFTs
#             with placeholder metadata; --hash + reveal
#             workflow for "blind mint" mechanics
#           - JSON CONFIG SCHEMA — config.json defines
#             collection, creators, royalties, max supply,
#             upload method, guard chain
#           - ANCHOR FRAMEWORK INTEGRATION — sugar uses
#             anchor-client + anchor-lang for typed Solana
#             RPC calls
#           - CLI MIRRORS THE Candy Machine v3 + Candy Guard v2
#             on-chain programs maintained at metaplex-
#             foundation/mpl-candy-machine + mpl-candy-guard
#         Used by: Solana NFT collection creators (PFP
#         projects, generative art, music NFTs, ticketing),
#         Metaplex's Sugar tutorials (the canonical Candy
#         Machine onboarding path), and as a reference
#         implementation of dialoguer + console + indicatif +
#         clap derive + anchor-client + tokio + bundlr-sdk
#         composition in production Rust.
