# Source:  https://github.com/metaplex-foundation/sugar
#          https://github.com/metaplex-foundation/sugar/blob/main/src/cli/mod.rs
#          https://github.com/metaplex-foundation/sugar/blob/main/src/main.rs
#          https://github.com/metaplex-foundation/sugar/blob/main/Cargo.toml
# CLI:     src/cli/mod.rs + src/main.rs — uses clap v3 derive
#          (#[derive(Parser)], #[derive(Subcommand)]).  Headline
#          library: **dialoguer** (clap is documented across
#          many Rust completions; dialoguer is the new variant
#          being documented here, populating Axis 8 — Interactive
#          Prompts).
# Library: dialoguer (https://github.com/console-rs/dialoguer —
#          "Rust utility library for nice command line prompts
#           and similar things" — Armin Ronacher (mitsuhiko
#           on GitHub) under the console-rs org.  Distinct from
#           all previously-documented Rust libraries by being:
#              1. INTERACTIVE PROMPT WIDGETS — provides a set
#                 of pre-built prompt widget types:
#                   * Input<T>          — text input with
#                                          default, validation,
#                                          history, allow_empty
#                   * Password          — masked password input
#                                          with optional confirm
#                   * Confirm           — yes/no with default
#                   * Select            — single-choice menu
#                   * MultiSelect       — multi-choice (space to
#                                          toggle, enter to confirm)
#                   * Sort              — interactive list
#                                          reordering
#                   * FuzzySelect       — typing-narrow filter
#                                          (requires `fuzzy-select`
#                                          feature)
#                   * Editor            — launch $EDITOR for
#                                          large text input
#              2. BUILDER PATTERN — each prompt is a struct with
#                 chainable setters:
#                   use dialoguer::{Input, theme::ColorfulTheme};
#                   let name: String = Input::with_theme(&ColorfulTheme::default())
#                       .with_prompt("Project name")
#                       .default("my-project".into())
#                       .interact_text()?;
#              3. CONSOLE-RS ECOSYSTEM INTEGRATION — built on
#                 the `console` crate (terminal manipulation:
#                 cursor positioning, terminal size, styled
#                 text, key reading); pairs with `indicatif`
#                 (progress bars) for full TUI feel
#              4. THEME SUPPORT via Theme trait — pluggable
#                 styling; ColorfulTheme (default, with colors
#                 + emoji), SimpleTheme (plain), or custom
#                 implementations.  Distinct from inquire which
#                 has a fixed theming model.
#              5. VALIDATION via Validator trait — `.validate_with`
#                 accepts a Fn(&T) -> Result<(), E>; prompt
#                 re-displays on validation failure:
#                   .validate_with(|input: &String| -> Result<(), &str> {
#                       if input.len() < 3 { Err("min 3 chars") }
#                       else { Ok(()) }
#                   })
#              6. HISTORY via History trait — input prompts can
#                 attach a History trait object for up-arrow
#                 recall of previous inputs.
#              7. NO ASYNC — purely synchronous; uses blocking
#                 read on stdin.  Distinct from inquire which
#                 also has no async but provides different
#                 fallback strategies for non-tty stdin.
#              8. ARMIN-RONACHER / MITSUHIKO / CONSOLE-RS
#                 ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE — Armin Ronacher
#                 (mitsuhiko) maintains the console-rs org
#                 with:
#                   * console      — terminal manipulation
#                   * dialoguer    — interactive prompts             (THIS)
#                   * indicatif    — progress bars
#                 plus his Python ecosystem (Flask, Jinja2,
#                 Click, MarkupSafe, Werkzeug), Rust crates
#                 (Sentry SDK, similar, insta, milksnake),
#                 and former GitHub Trending.
#              9. NO RUNTIME DEPS BEYOND console — minimal
#                 dependency footprint (console + optional
#                 fuzzy-matcher for FuzzySelect).
#             10. STABLE v0.10 API SINCE 2021 — well-tested,
#                 widely-adopted; current API is essentially
#                 unchanged across 0.10/0.11/0.12 series.)
# License: MIT (dialoguer); Apache-2.0 (sugar)
# Status:  dialoguer — 1,597+ stars on console-rs/dialoguer,
